==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foozle
<hw>Foo"zle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Foozled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Foozling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. G.
<ets>fuseln</ets> to work badly or slowly.]</ety> <def>To bungle; to
manage awkwardly; to treat or play unskillfully; <as>as, to
<ex>foozle</ex> a stroke in golf</as>.</def></p>

<p><q>She <qex>foozles</qex> all along the course.</q> <rj><qau>Century
Mag.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foozle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Foozle
<hw>Foo"zle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A stupid fellow; a
fogy.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Act of foozling; a bungling stroke, as in
golf.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fop</ent>⟦br⟧
